==Usage== <!--T:5-->

<!--T:6-->
# Place the cursor over geometry in the [[3D_View|3D View]].
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Clarify Selection}} option from the 3D View context menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|G}} then {{KEY|G}}.
#* When using the OpenInventor, Gesture or OpenSCAD [[Mouse_navigation|navigation style]]: hold {{KEY|Ctrl}} and press the left mouse button.
#* When using any other navigation style: hold the left mouse button for as long as defined by the ''Long press timeout'' [[Preferences_Editor#Navigation|preference]] (1 second by default).
# A menu listing object types appears next to the cursor. Depending on the objects near the cursor, it may include:
#* {{MenuCommand|Object}}
#* {{MenuCommand|Face}}
#* {{MenuCommand|Edge}}
#* {{MenuCommand|Vertex}}
#* {{MenuCommand|Other}}
# Choose an object type.
# Move the cursor over the submenu that appears. Hovered submenu items are highlighted in the 3D View.
# Click an item to select it.


